docs.snippet: MADRID, Dec. 28. -- After carefully considering all evidence presented by the Attorney General against the former Socialist Premier Manuel Azana and his former secretary, Luis Bello, the Spanish Supreme Court today decided there was no grounds for an...
docs.lead_paragraph: MADRID, Dec. 28. -- After carefully considering all evidence presented by the Attorney General against the former Socialist Premier Manuel Azana and his former secretary, Luis Bello, the Spanish Supreme Court today decided there was no grounds for an indictment. Orders were telegraphed to Barcelona for the immediate release of the two.
